The paper proposes a subspace constrained precoding scheme for massive MIMO cellular systems, which involves optimization problems related to channel state information, interference mitigation, and quality of service. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication systems. The paper also involves network optimization and control, which suggests the sub-categories cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Systems and Control). The use of massive MIMO technology and the evaluation of simulation results suggest the sub-categories cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
